<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="178" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="178">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="178">Europe.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="178" type="prey">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="178">Prey.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="178">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Cacopsylla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cacopsylla melanoneura" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanoneura">Cacopsylla melanoneura</taxonomicName>
, from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Malus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Malus domestica" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="domestica">Malus domestica</taxonomicName>
, Beloljin, 4.V.2008, collected 1♂; Ilinci, 20.V.2006, reared 1♂ 'ex larva' 25.V.2006; Uzovnica, 29.IV.2007, collected 1 specimen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="178">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Heterocordylus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heterocordylus genistae" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="genistae">Heterocordylus genistae</taxonomicName>
is mentioned in the literature as a beneficial insect being a predator of psyllids both in larval and adult stage. It is registered as a predator of various other insects (
<bibRefCitation author="Protic, Lj" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. Belgrade, Serbia: University of Belgrade, Faculty of Agriculture" pageId="14" pageNumber="183" title="Proucavanje faune stenica (Heteroptera) u vocnim zasadima Srbije." year="1993">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Protić">Protic</normalizedToken>
1993
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Protic, Lj" journalOrPublisher="Special issue" pageId="15" pageNumber="184" pagination="1 - 215" title="Catalogue of the Heteroptera fauna of Yugoslav countries. Part one. Natural History Museum, Belgrade." volume="38" year="1998">1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="178">
In the present paper, we report 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Heterocordylus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heterocordylus genistae" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="genistae">Heterocordylus genistae</taxonomicName>
for the first time as a predator of psyllids in Serbia.
</paragraph>
